scripts/kshfuncs/
ksh functions.  Intended to be sourced at login time or at time of first
invokation by using the FPATH ksh variable (see the ksh man page).
They may work with pd-ksh, bash, or zsh as well (possibly with some porting).

Filename   Description
bang       Retrieve words from command history; like csh ! but less convenient.
dirs       Lists directory history maintained by ucd (see below).
history    Replacement for ksh's built-in history (fc -l) command.
ucd        Replacement for cd; does directory history and database lookup, etc.

